  "market_context": "Light Crude Oil Futures on a 15-minute chart. During the London session, price retraced lower but failed to reach a relevant higher time frame level. Price continued lower into the New York session, eventually sweeping the previous day low marked as Sell-Side Liquidity near 77.89.",
  "key_observation": "London failed to reach the key HTF level (previous day low / Sell-Side Liquidity ~77.89). New York extended the move lower to sweep that level, triggering a Change in State of Delivery and a subsequent bullish continuation through multiple failure swings.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the previous day low as the Sell-Side Liquidity target (~77.89) and marked it as the key HTF reference level on the 15-minute CL1! chart.",
    "Step 2: Observed that during the London session, price retraced lower but never reached the Sell-Side Liquidity level, confirming this was not a London Reversal profile.",
    "Step 3: Watched price continue lower into the New York session, where it finally reached and swept the Sell-Side Liquidity level (~77.89), completing the HTF target.",
    "Step 4: Marked the series of down-closed candles at the New York session low to identify the potential Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH) trigger level.",
    "Step 5: Observed an initial failed attempt to close above the down-closed candle series, which signaled price could make a new low or push further into the wick before reversing.",
    "Step 6: After price made a new low, identified a new series of down-closed candles aligning with the New York open time level as the updated CHoCH reference.",
    "Step 7: Waited for a candle close above the new down-closed candle series to confirm the Change in State of Delivery and frame a long trade entry.",
    "Step 8: Set the stop-loss at the bottom of the identified order block (rather than the swing low) to improve risk-to-reward, and targeted the cluster of failure swings above as the take-profit.",
    "Step 9: Confirmed the trade played out as anticipated — price continued higher, taking out all the failure swings above, completing the bullish New York Reversal profile."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long trade triggered after CHoCH confirmation at New York open. Price continued higher, taking out all failure swings above. Trade was profitable with stop placed at the bottom of the order block.",
  "lessons": "When London retraces but fails to reach a key HTF level, classify the day as a potential New York Reversal. Wait for New York to sweep the HTF level, confirm a Change in State of Delivery, then enter in the reversal direction targeting failure swings above (or below for bearish).",
